            "examples": [
                {
                    "id": "aerosol_size_distribution_curves",
                    "description": "The canonical Seinfeld & Pandis Chapter 8 figure: the Urban multi-modal lognormal aerosol size distribution. Sweeps the evaluation diameter D_p logarithmically across the full atmospheric aerosol range (1 nm to 10 um) and plots the number (n_N_o, Eq. 8.54), surface-area (n_S_o, Eq. 8.49/8.50) and volume (n_V_o, Eq. 8.52/8.53) distribution densities. The characteristic shift of the distribution peak toward larger diameters going from number to surface to volume is the headline result of this section.",
